four times already.

13:38.659 --> 13:40.892
Hey,
hey, hey, come on.

13:40.894 --> 13:43.628
I don't wanna hear none of
that holier than thou bullshit.

13:43.630 --> 13:45.765
Now don't you make an ass
outta me down there today.

13:45.767 --> 13:46.866
'Cause I don't even
wanna be here right now

13:46.868 --> 13:47.867
- with you, huh?
- Boy.

13:47.869 --> 13:49.035
I'm tired of your shit.

13:49.037 --> 13:49.835
- I pay for your pillow!
- I'm tired of you

13:49.837 --> 13:50.803
touchin' me, I'm tired

13:50.805 --> 13:51.737
- of your shit.
- Hey, hey, hey.

13:51.739 --> 13:52.704
Hey, you get back here, boy.

13:52.706 --> 13:53.542
Boy!

13:55.877 --> 13:58.478
Hey, 18 all right?

13:58.480 --> 13:59.545
All right?

13:59.547 --> 14:00.479
He is 18.

14:00.481 --> 14:02.547
We was both in the
fuckin' war at 18, John.

14:02.549 --> 14:03.882
I know that, Kenny.

14:03.884 --> 14:04.916
Now he's just a boy,
and he's got a bit

14:04.918 --> 14:06.618
of your blood in him.

14:06.620 --> 14:07.755
Now go sit down.

14:11.826 --> 14:12.992
What'd I tell
you about drinkin'

14:12.994 --> 14:15.093
before your shift, Kenny, huh?

14:15.095 --> 14:16.764
What did I tell you?

14:22.470 --> 14:23.603
- Stop!
- Go home.

14:23.605 --> 14:24.773
- Ryan!
- What?

14:25.672 --> 14:27.172
You don't have to do this.

14:27.174 --> 14:29.074
Listen, my dad ain't like
your parents, Missy, all right?

14:29.076 --> 14:30.877
What don't you
understand about this?

14:30.879 --> 14:32.145
I don't have time to sit

14:32.147 --> 14:33.612
in this damn town
and wait for you.

14:33.614 --> 14:35.915
And I'm not able
to go with you.

14:35.917 --> 14:39.021
I don't even have
gas money, ya know?

14:41.889 --> 14:44.058
Happy birthday, Russell.

14:45.427 --> 14:46.726
What do you say, Russell?

14:46.728 --> 14:47.730
Thank you.

14:48.863 --> 14:49.698
Grace.

14:52.600 --> 14:53.435
Hi, Susie.

14:54.168 --> 14:55.002
Hi.

14:56.937 --> 14:59.704
Did you get the call
about the reunion?

14:59.706 --> 15:00.742
Yeah.

15:03.445 --> 15:04.776
Are ya goin'?

15:04.778 --> 15:06.612
You have a good day, Teresa.

15:06.614 --> 15:07.612
Hey, Russell.

15:07.614 --> 15:08.446
And I hope you and Salvia

15:08.448 --> 15:11.519
are takin' good
care of my husband.

15:12.619 --> 15:13.755
Have a good day.

15:18.192 --> 15:21.761
Shame on you, Daniel, for
goin' back down there.

15:21.763 --> 15:23.996
Shame on all of y'all!

15:23.998 --> 15:25.897
I ain't sittin'
here another minute.

15:27.469 --> 15:29.234
Russell, get to the car.

15:29.236 --> 15:30.670
Get.

15:36.244 --> 15:39.078
Two hours, fellas, two hours.

15:39.080 --> 15:42.647
♪ He loves guitar ♪

15:42.649 --> 15:44.483
♪ But he's just gone ♪

15:52.627 --> 15:54.627
Teresa, wait up.

15:54.629 --> 15:55.696
What is it?

15:57.764 --> 15:59.265
The sump pump on Nine
is on life support.

15:59.267 --> 16:01.000
All right, I'll put in
another work order, then.

16:01.002 --> 16:02.901
Work orders don't mean
shit around here, Teresa,

16:02.903 --> 16:04.170
everybody knows that.

16:04.172 --> 16:05.704
Hell, we don't even
have a mine rescue.

16:05.706 --> 16:06.738
You ain't diggin' enough coal,

16:06.740 --> 16:07.873
so they're forced to make cuts.

16:07.875 --> 16:09.709
Oh that's bullshit.

16:09.711 --> 16:14.048
We dig more goddamn coal
than any mine in this area!

16:17.685 --> 16:18.754
My apologies.

16:21.589 --> 16:22.821
But the old works are
leakin' more methane

16:22.823 --> 16:24.189
than I've seen in 30 years.

16:24.191 --> 16:25.558
Where's the outside
foreman, huh?

16:25.560 --> 16:26.659
He's still sick.

16:26.661 --> 16:28.230
And no replacement?

16:30.831 --> 16:34.666
When those pumps give
out, and they will,

16:34.668 --> 16:37.670
then my men are gonna
drown two miles in,

16:37.672 --> 16:40.776
unless an ignition
burns us up first.

16:41.808 --> 16:43.642
What are you gonna do?

16:43.644 --> 16:45.545
Are you gonna call MSHA?

16:45.547 --> 16:47.747
And what happens
if I call MSHA, huh?

16:47.749 --> 16:50.016
What happens when
MSHA shows up here?

16:50.018 --> 16:52.885
They're gonna shut us down
and we're all screwed.

16:52.887 --> 16:54.119
Is that what you want?

16:54.121 --> 16:57.823
Everyone on your
crew starts on time.

16:57.825 --> 16:59.595
Is that understood?

17:03.630 --> 17:05.099
That's understood.

17:13.807 --> 17:16.007
I am well aware that
just by makin' this call

17:16.009 --> 17:17.877
I could be shuttin' us down,

17:17.878 --> 17:20.845
and my men are not onboard
I want you to know,

17:20.847 --> 17:22.681
but if somethin' were to happen,

17:22.683 --> 17:26.218
we got no mine rescue, we
got no outside foreman.

17:26.220 --> 17:28.588
It seems to me that
corporate cares more

17:28.590 --> 17:30.790
about their coal reserves
and their machinery

17:30.792 --> 17:33.159
than they do about their miners.

17:33.161 --> 17:34.660
All right, well, we
will open up a case

17:34.662 --> 17:36.829
first thing Monday morning.

17:36.831 --> 17:40.766
Now I called MSHA to help
us today, not on Monday.

17:40.768 --> 17:42.801
I understand, but
Mine Safety and Health

17:42.803 --> 17:44.302
is not in the business
of shuttin' down

17:44.304 --> 17:46.638
a mine without an investigation.

17:46.640 --> 17:49.875
I got men goin' into that
mine tonight, do you understand?

17:49.877 --> 17:51.711
I am fully aware,
but it's gonna

17:51.713 --> 17:54.249
have to wait 'til
Monday mornin'.

17:55.882 --> 17:58.350
Yes, sir, thank you very much.

17:58.352 --> 17:59.554
All right.

20:00.742 --> 20:01.677
Hey, son.

20:15.022 --> 20:17.024
That's break 23, John.

20:18.359 --> 20:19.892
It's gettin' worse.

20:19.894 --> 20:20.962
Yeah, got it.

20:49.023 --> 20:50.388
Hey, red hat.

20:50.390 --> 20:52.390
Psst, hey, kid.

20:52.392 --> 20:56.561
Your dad ever told about
Matt and Ben Fellows?

20:56.563 --> 20:57.398
Naw.

20:58.299 --> 21:01.099
You ain't never told him?

21:01.101 --> 21:03.002
No, he didn't tell me.

21:03.004 --> 21:05.271
Oh hell, they both worked
this whole section here

21:05.273 --> 21:07.438
a piece back, good boys.

21:07.440 --> 21:10.509
But since it's your first
time goin' underground,

21:10.511 --> 21:12.077
I just thought maybe you should

21:12.079 --> 21:14.012
just know somethin' about 'em.

21:14.014 --> 21:14.980
Why?

21:14.982 --> 21:15.947
Why?

21:15.949 --> 21:18.349
Matt and Ben's first
eight days underground,

21:18.351 --> 21:20.852
after every single shift,
they'd come out here

21:20.854 --> 21:24.123
and said they seen
somethin', and it was on the,

21:24.125 --> 21:27.458
what was it, ninth, ninth day?

21:27.460 --> 21:29.194
Ninth day they
said Satan appeared

21:29.196 --> 21:30.562
and he said if
you ever come back

21:30.564 --> 21:33.866
down here again,
boys, you gon' die.

21:33.868 --> 21:34.869
Hey hold up.

21:39.540 --> 21:41.909
Did they come back down?

21:44.378 --> 21:45.379
Hey, Daniel.

21:46.613 --> 21:48.047
- Dad.
- He'll tell ya.

21:48.049 --> 21:49.181
Did they
come back down?

21:49.183 --> 21:52.083
Daniel'll tell you
in a minute, now.

21:52.085 --> 21:54.153
Oh hell, they
didn't have a choice.

21:54.155 --> 21:56.588
They have to work, right?

21:56.590 --> 21:58.991
Yeah, but if we just
say hey, you know,

21:58.993 --> 22:01.092
make it through what, 10 days?

22:01.094 --> 22:04.296
You're good to go.

22:04.298 --> 22:06.031
Yeah, it's moments like that

22:06.033 --> 22:08.500
you come face to face with God.

22:08.502 --> 22:10.806
Yeah, or Satan himself.

22:12.005 --> 22:13.340
What happened?

22:14.375 --> 22:15.177
Huh?

22:16.142 --> 22:18.444
What happened to 'em?

22:18.446 --> 22:19.947
Do I tell him?

22:21.081 --> 22:23.985
The roof fell and
them boys dead.

22:27.254 --> 22:32.194
They're here one second,
gone the next.

22:33.360 --> 22:36.561
Cuttin' coal is
risky business, son.

22:36.563 --> 22:39.098
Gotta hold your own
down here, understood?

22:39.100 --> 22:40.001
Yes, sir.

22:41.167 --> 22:42.533
And that story he told ya

22:42.535 --> 22:46.006
about them boys dyin'
what got crushed?

22:47.207 --> 22:48.240
That's a lie, we're
just jokin' with ya.

22:54.648 --> 22:57.316
But men do hallucinate,
the methane gets to 'em.

22:57.318 --> 23:01.486
Heaven, Hell, angels, demons,
I don't know men seen 'em all.

23:01.488 --> 23:06.224
♪ Coal miner, coal miner
shinin' your light ♪

23:06.226 --> 23:10.561
♪ Workin' on a mineshaft
dark as the night ♪

23:10.563 --> 23:14.399
♪ Whatcha gonna do
before ya go back in ♪

23:14.401 --> 23:19.407
♪ I'm gonna ask the Lord
to let me come out again ♪

23:20.308 --> 23:22.407
Ow-ooh, ow, ow, ow, ow, ooh!

23:22.409 --> 23:24.042
Yeah, I was
just messin' with ya, boy.

23:24.044 --> 23:25.109
One more time!

23:26.147 --> 23:30.950
♪ Coal miner, coal miner
shinin' your light ♪

23:30.952 --> 23:34.720
♪ Workin' on a mineshaft
dark as the night ♪

23:34.722 --> 23:38.723
♪ Whatcha gonna do
before ya go back in ♪

23:38.725 --> 23:43.931
♪ I'm gonna ask the Lord
to let me come out again ♪

23:45.032 --> 23:47.101
Ow-ooh, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

24:44.358 --> 24:45.527
What number?

24:47.360 --> 24:48.694
Number
seven, isn't it?

24:58.671 --> 24:59.673
Hey, Ryan.

25:00.541 --> 25:02.010
Now looky here.

25:03.310 --> 25:05.410
You need to know the
escape ways outta here

25:05.412 --> 25:06.611
should anything ever happen.

25:06.613 --> 25:08.646
All right, yeah.

25:08.648 --> 25:11.082
Right, so here's
the old works,

25:11.084 --> 25:13.117
North Main, South Main.

25:13.119 --> 25:14.787
Those are the three
lines into this place.

25:14.789 --> 25:15.954
Yeah.

25:15.956 --> 25:18.190
Now the primary escape way
is the way we just come in

25:18.192 --> 25:20.692
through the entrance track.

25:20.694 --> 25:22.327
- Yeah.
- Secondary is up

25:22.329 --> 25:25.164
through the fan house
along the conveyor passage.

25:25.166 --> 25:26.330
Belt, the...

25:26.332 --> 25:27.398
The belt that's
right here, right here.

25:27.400 --> 25:28.634
That's where the conveyor runs.

25:28.636 --> 25:30.335
All right.

25:30.337 --> 25:33.338
Now, if all else fails,
you get your ass right here.

25:33.340 --> 25:35.441
This is the North Main Chamber.

25:35.443 --> 25:36.675
Yes sir, yes sir.

25:36.677 --> 25:38.543
Hey, right here,
North Main Chamber.

25:38.545 --> 25:39.744
North Main Chamber.

25:39.746 --> 25:41.213
It's where we
got a refuge cache,

25:41.215 --> 25:43.714
which has got air,
tools, and whatnot.

25:43.716 --> 25:44.817
Refuge catch?

25:44.819 --> 25:45.851
- Cache.
- Cache.

25:45.853 --> 25:49.620
Refuge, your daddy
calls it a safety coffin.

25:49.622 --> 25:52.790
Why does he call
it a safety coffin?

25:52.792 --> 25:54.827
Safety, well, 'cause
the fuckin' thing

25:54.829 --> 25:57.262
is shaped like a damn coffin.

25:57.264 --> 25:58.329
- Right?
- Yeah.

26:00.467 --> 26:03.335
And if you need it, you're
probably dead already.

26:03.337 --> 26:06.804
But, some shit hit the
fan, I guarantee you

26:06.806 --> 26:09.309
they'd call it a refuge cache.

26:12.279 --> 26:13.415
Hey, looky here.

26:15.381 --> 26:17.683
I been doin' this
damn near 30 years.

26:17.685 --> 26:21.752
Your family has got almost
two centuries underground.

26:21.754 --> 26:22.788
Yeah.

26:22.790 --> 26:24.459
Gon' be fine, son.

26:25.892 --> 26:27.326
- Yeah.
- All right.

26:27.328 --> 26:28.760
Now you go over there,
have Daniel show you

26:28.762 --> 26:30.361
how to bolt the roof.

26:30.363 --> 26:31.496
Yes, sir.

26:31.498 --> 26:34.368
You
wanna shut that off?

26:37.338 --> 26:38.373
Yo, hey.

26:39.340 --> 26:40.638
Shut it off, man.

26:40.640 --> 26:41.642
Shut it off!

26:46.312 --> 26:48.780
Damn.

26:48.782 --> 26:52.150
Hey yo, are we makin' that
damn turn yet or what?

26:52.152 --> 26:55.186
No, we still got
three full cuts today.

26:55.188 --> 26:57.556
Go to short cuts if ya have to.

26:57.558 --> 27:00.259
And no more rock fallin'
through, Rooster.

27:00.261 --> 27:01.792
I don't give a
shit about the rocks!

27:01.794 --> 27:03.729
The dust what's gonna kill us!

27:03.731 --> 27:04.730
Yeah, I hear ya.

27:04.732 --> 27:06.464
Tiny, get back there and see

27:06.466 --> 27:09.201
if you can fix that
suppression control.

27:09.203 --> 27:10.801
And wet us down
before we flame up.

27:10.803 --> 27:13.440
Yes, sir, I'm on it.

27:25.418 --> 27:27.319
Look right here.

27:27.321 --> 27:28.419
What we got here is
our plate, all right?

27:28.421 --> 27:29.620
All right,
all right, okay.

27:29.622 --> 27:30.688
See this right here?

27:30.690 --> 27:32.191
This what, hey, focus, man.

27:32.193 --> 27:33.457
That's how you get
hurt down here.

27:33.459 --> 27:34.658
- All right?
- Yeah.

27:34.660 --> 27:38.463
It's what keeps these mines
from droppin' on our head.

27:38.465 --> 27:41.233
Straight hole, straight
bolt, loose pin set.

27:41.235 --> 27:41.867
Ya got it?

27:41.869 --> 27:42.967
Yeah.

27:47.574 --> 27:48.773
Come on.

27:48.775 --> 27:50.208
Get up!

27:50.210 --> 27:53.444
Nothin' but a shift
in the roof, come on.

27:53.446 --> 27:56.647
Get used to it,
happens all the time.

27:56.649 --> 27:57.582
- Hey, hey.
- Don't wanna die

27:57.584 --> 27:58.817
Take a deep breath, breathe.

27:58.819 --> 28:01.523
Boo!

28:02.356 --> 28:03.488
Everybody all right?

28:03.490 --> 28:05.456
Yeah, that rookie's all right.

28:05.458 --> 28:07.326
Get it fixed.

28:07.328 --> 28:09.261
If you need help, ask for it.

28:09.263 --> 28:10.428
- Hey, Rooster.
- Ho!

28:10.430 --> 28:11.597
Get that miner goin'.

28:11.599 --> 28:12.763
Change of plans.

28:12.765 --> 28:14.398
We're goin' down
entry one before long.

28:14.400 --> 28:15.967
Hold it!

28:15.969 --> 28:19.637
Ryan, get back to
dustin' walls, go on.

28:19.639 --> 28:22.374
Boss, I'm gonna get down to
that power station, all right?

28:22.376 --> 28:25.743
All right, well
be quick about it.

28:53.407 --> 28:55.339
You hear that?

28:55.341 --> 28:56.774
Y'all can hear that?

29:00.014 --> 29:02.550
Hey, we gotta move.

29:14.527 --> 29:16.697
She's comin' down, boys!

29:18.331 --> 29:20.598
Run, run, out, out,
past the rim, go!

29:20.600 --> 29:21.767
Dad!

29:21.769 --> 29:24.839
Everybody, everybody,
pass the rim.

29:25.872 --> 29:27.571
Everybody, out past the rim.

29:27.573 --> 29:29.540
Past the rim, move!

29:29.542 --> 29:30.378
Kenny!

29:32.946 --> 29:34.849
Kenny, Kenny, let's go.

29:36.317 --> 29:37.785
You trust it to God.

29:40.053 --> 29:41.255
Come on, go!

29:47.960 --> 29:49.727
Zeke, Zeke!

29:49.729 --> 29:50.564
Daniel!

30:29.570 --> 30:30.672
Judas Priest.

30:31.972 --> 30:34.505
We got ripped through.

30:34.507 --> 30:37.041
Yeah, we
got ripped through.

30:37.043 --> 30:38.076
Ryan!

30:40.747 --> 30:41.579
Ryan!

30:41.581 --> 30:42.850
Oh no.

30:46.887 --> 30:49.057
Ryan, Ryan, you all right?

30:50.556 --> 30:52.758
You all right, son?

30:52.760 --> 30:54.992
Did ya get pegged?

31:13.580 --> 31:18.552
Damn.

31:18.985 --> 31:20.685
God saved us.

31:20.687 --> 31:23.088
God saved us, did He?

31:23.090 --> 31:24.556
Well, you go ahead and thank Him

31:24.558 --> 31:26.892
for puttin' us plum in
the middle of this shit.

31:26.894 --> 31:29.094
We lost Harper, Tiny.

31:29.096 --> 31:30.829
Miller's dead.

31:30.831 --> 31:32.062
It's okay, son.

31:32.064 --> 31:34.733
Think maybe we should
pray for him, then.

31:34.735 --> 31:35.833
Where's Daniel?

31:35.835 --> 31:37.469
I saw Daniel.

31:37.471 --> 31:38.569
It don't look good.

31:38.571 --> 31:39.905
Shit, no.

31:39.907 --> 31:41.873
Hey, you know
you killed me, huh?

31:41.875 --> 31:43.207
You know I'm gonna die down here

31:43.209 --> 31:44.443
- because of you?
- Hey!

31:44.445 --> 31:46.477
Listen, son, you listen good.

31:46.479 --> 31:47.846
- You keep your shit together.
- Knock it off!

31:47.848 --> 31:49.047
- Now or never!
- Who knows

31:49.049 --> 31:50.915
which direction that
blast came from?

31:50.917 --> 31:52.951
I thought it came from out
behind the Mains back there.

31:52.953 --> 31:54.552
Mains is that way.

31:54.554 --> 31:57.755
Kenny's right, Kenny's right.

31:57.757 --> 32:01.126
My back was facin'
somewhere, out by the mouth.

32:01.128 --> 32:02.927
I think it came
from behind me.

32:02.929 --> 32:06.097
I think whichever
way we choose,

32:06.099 --> 32:08.833
we're still a long way from
the Mains no matter what.

32:08.835 --> 32:09.937
Yes we are.

32:13.706 --> 32:15.773
- Shit.
- All right.

32:15.775 --> 32:18.643
Well let's spread out and
find those boys, all right.

32:18.645 --> 32:20.611
And if they didn't make it,
then just put 'em together

32:20.613 --> 32:22.716
so that others can find 'em.

32:26.552 --> 32:30.088
And strip 'em of their
lights and rescuers,

32:30.090 --> 32:32.624
tools, curtains, anything,
anything we can find

32:32.626 --> 32:34.626
to help us get outta
here, all right?

32:34.628 --> 32:36.160
Spread out and
let's get workin'.

32:36.162 --> 32:37.695
All right.

32:37.697 --> 32:39.630
All right, boys, holler out.

32:39.632 --> 32:42.934
Harper!

32:42.936 --> 32:44.205
- Harper!
- Hello?

32:51.744 --> 32:52.580
Help.

32:53.780 --> 32:54.646
Hello?

33:00.052 --> 33:00.888
Help.

33:03.823 --> 33:04.658
Daniel!

33:08.794 --> 33:10.262
Oh, Tiny.

33:10.264 --> 33:13.264
He just had a newborn, James.

33:13.266 --> 33:14.100
Come on.

33:15.235 --> 33:15.869
Oh.

33:19.773 --> 33:22.009
Our Father who art in heaven.

33:35.688 --> 33:37.757
Coal miner, coal miner.

33:43.796 --> 33:46.033
I can get ya home, brother.

34:03.350 --> 34:06.350
Thy kingdom
come, thy will be done

34:06.352 --> 34:08.786
on Earth as it is in heaven.

34:08.789 --> 34:10.722
Give us this day our daily bread

34:10.724 --> 34:12.056
and forgive us our trespasses

34:12.059 --> 34:15.694
as we forgive those who
trespass against us.

34:15.696 --> 34:18.163
Lead us not into temptation.

34:34.982 --> 34:38.786
I'm sorry, man.

34:47.293 --> 34:52.033
Let's go, let's go,
let's go.

35:02.209 --> 35:05.745
Us from evil, for
thine is the kingdom

35:06.879 --> 35:09.747
and the power and glory.

35:09.749 --> 35:10.917
Forever, amen.

35:12.318 --> 35:13.987
God bless you, Tiny.

35:16.055 --> 35:18.059
Sorry, I'm sorry, buddy.

35:24.898 --> 35:26.698
All right, let's go.

35:26.700 --> 35:27.802
There's more.

35:29.436 --> 35:31.669
What about
Daniel and Smitty?

35:31.671 --> 35:34.039
Smitty's right
over here behind me.

35:34.041 --> 35:35.939
I suggest ya leave him be.

35:35.941 --> 35:37.175
No.

35:37.177 --> 35:38.977
All right, gather up
anything and everything

35:38.979 --> 35:42.814
you can find and put
it in the powder bag.

35:42.816 --> 35:44.214
If I'm right about the explosion

35:44.216 --> 35:46.718
and we find the North
Main, we can hole up there

35:46.720 --> 35:49.023
and hope that someone arrives.

35:50.957 --> 35:51.823
All right, let's move.

35:51.825 --> 35:53.227
Be careful, fellas.

35:54.260 --> 35:55.862
- All right!
- Yeah.

35:56.930 --> 35:58.830
Eh, get the boy.

35:58.832 --> 36:00.198
Come on, boy.

36:00.200 --> 36:02.100
I see ya back 'ere.

36:02.102 --> 36:02.937
Come on.

36:11.711 --> 36:14.479
I found the lifeline.

36:14.481 --> 36:16.751
See that there?

36:19.151 --> 36:21.856
- There we go.
- Look at that.

36:22.988 --> 36:24.891
Watch your foot.

36:37.037 --> 36:38.135
Hey, Kenny.

36:38.137 --> 36:39.236
You feel that, Zeke?

36:39.238 --> 36:40.171
What's that?

36:40.173 --> 36:41.805
The fan's still runnin'.

36:41.807 --> 36:43.173
That's a good
sign, little brother,

36:43.175 --> 36:44.978
that's a good sign.

36:46.912 --> 36:48.879
Damn it!

36:48.881 --> 36:51.883
Goddamn it, the whole
fuckin' panel's caved in.

36:51.885 --> 36:53.151
Well which way now?

36:53.153 --> 36:55.252
Well I guess we gotta
find a secondary, John.

36:55.254 --> 36:56.854
Well what if we
find an old route

36:56.856 --> 36:58.222
out through the travel road?

36:58.224 --> 37:00.225
Naw, naw, there's
a fire down here.

37:00.227 --> 37:02.926
It's surely gon' be burnin'
there, by the old works?

37:02.928 --> 37:03.764
Come on.

37:05.966 --> 37:06.930
Oh for God's sake, Kenny.

37:06.932 --> 37:08.334
Goddamn it, really?

37:10.803 --> 37:14.108
We're in a world of
shit no matter what.

37:17.042 --> 37:17.975
John.

37:17.977 --> 37:19.144
What?

37:19.146 --> 37:21.211
Don't you dare.

37:21.213 --> 37:22.981
I was there when you
got your 10 year chip,

37:22.983 --> 37:24.515
do you remember that?

37:24.517 --> 37:25.783
Yeah.

37:25.785 --> 37:27.919
- You remember that?
- Yeah.

37:27.921 --> 37:30.925
Remember how hard
fought that was?

37:31.957 --> 37:32.726
Yeah.

37:33.894 --> 37:36.361
We're gon' get outta here.

37:36.363 --> 37:37.732
And then what?

37:44.937 --> 37:45.939
There ya go.

37:53.146 --> 37:55.446
You go ahead, son.

37:55.448 --> 37:57.084
You deserve that.

38:05.224 --> 38:07.859
Fellas, there's
somethin' I gotta tell you.

38:07.861 --> 38:09.026
What?

38:09.028 --> 38:10.127
I called MSHA.

38:10.129 --> 38:11.329
Aw!

38:11.331 --> 38:12.897
I told 'em we
got no mine rescue,

38:12.899 --> 38:13.997
I told 'em about the methane,

38:13.999 --> 38:17.368
I told 'em about the pumps,
I told 'em all of it.

38:17.370 --> 38:18.870
Well then you
fuckin' killed us

38:18.872 --> 38:20.004
we don't dig
ourselves outta here.

38:20.006 --> 38:21.439
Teresa woulda sent
the second shift

38:21.441 --> 38:23.106
down to help dig us out.

38:23.108 --> 38:24.975
You wanna put those boys
in danger, too, right?

38:24.977 --> 38:25.943
Is that you?

38:25.945 --> 38:27.010
- Is that what you want?
- What do you mean?

38:27.012 --> 38:27.946
What do you mean?

38:27.948 --> 38:29.513
I tell you what it means.

38:29.515 --> 38:33.984
If MSHA knows that we
aint' got no mine rescue,

38:33.986 --> 38:37.254
they ain't sendin' no men
into a tickin' time bomb.

38:37.256 --> 38:38.289
That's what that means.

38:38.291 --> 38:39.223
What?

38:39.225 --> 38:40.959
By the book, Zeke.

38:40.961 --> 38:43.627
You always gotta be
by the fuckin' book.

38:43.629 --> 38:44.461
We voted!

38:44.463 --> 38:46.065
Yeah, we voted.

38:47.566 --> 38:51.035
Now we are down here
on our own, fellas.

38:51.037 --> 38:53.171
And if you wanna live,
we gotta stick together.

38:53.173 --> 38:55.106
Is that understood,
little brother?

38:55.108 --> 38:56.640
John, grab a hold
of that lifeline

38:56.642 --> 38:58.376
and you get us back to the
Mains, you understand me?

38:58.378 --> 38:59.209
Yes, sir.

38:59.211 --> 39:01.012
Come on, Kenny.

39:02.182 --> 39:03.548
Oh boy.

39:03.550 --> 39:05.082
You just keep movin'.

39:05.084 --> 39:06.251
All right, boys.

39:18.398 --> 39:21.531
Number Nine, can you hear me?

39:21.533 --> 39:23.434
Number Nine, can you hear me?

39:25.070 --> 39:25.905
Damn it.

39:40.519 --> 39:42.553
Mine
Safety and Health.

39:42.555 --> 39:45.122
Hello, this is Teresa
Lang, mine manager at Salvia.

39:45.124 --> 39:46.290
This is an emergency.

39:46.292 --> 39:48.059
Transferrin' now.

39:55.035 --> 39:55.870
Power.

40:05.211 --> 40:07.278
We gotta slow down.

40:07.280 --> 40:09.080
I can't get a breath.

40:34.640 --> 40:36.374
Oh, we got smoke, boys.

40:36.376 --> 40:38.042
Move, we got smoke!

40:38.044 --> 40:39.109
- Go, go, go, go, go!
- Go, go!

40:39.111 --> 40:40.044
Let's go, go.

40:40.046 --> 40:41.278
We gotta!

40:41.280 --> 40:42.113
Put up a curtain,
get a curtain up.

40:42.115 --> 40:43.247
Get that curtain up!

40:45.517 --> 40:46.686
Pull it tight.

40:49.155 --> 40:50.120
Keep goin'.

40:50.122 --> 40:51.622
Hold it, put that there.

40:51.624 --> 40:55.629
Yes sir, pull
it tight, just like that.

40:57.062 --> 40:58.997
Cover that hole,
boys, cover that hole.

40:58.999 --> 41:00.097
Ready for the pull.

41:01.133 --> 41:02.466
Get it in there.

41:32.298 --> 41:34.401
Hey, Ryan, grab your hammer.

41:35.702 --> 41:37.568
Looky here, just pound
up on the roof post

41:37.570 --> 41:38.602
three times, all right?

41:38.604 --> 41:39.803
Yeah.

41:39.805 --> 41:43.142
Then wait a few
seconds, pound again.

41:43.809 --> 41:45.609
Like that over and over.

41:45.611 --> 41:48.713
It's a long shot,
but maybe ,

41:48.715 --> 41:50.481
maybe the surface'll hear us.

41:50.483 --> 41:51.415
Right here?

41:51.417 --> 41:53.517
Just right on the plate.

41:57.356 --> 41:59.692
Hold on, wait, wait, listen.

42:11.604 --> 42:13.273
All right, go ahead.

42:16.776 --> 42:18.242
God.

42:22.347 --> 42:24.314
- We need help!
- Hey, hey, hey!

42:24.316 --> 42:27.385
- Help!
- Come on now, listen, listen.

42:27.387 --> 42:28.118
Save it.

42:28.120 --> 42:30.521
Gonna need every
last bit of air.

42:30.523 --> 42:31.856
Very good.

42:31.858 --> 42:33.256
Ryan, Ryan, look at me.

42:33.258 --> 42:34.624
It's okay.

42:37.262 --> 42:38.129
Come on.

42:38.131 --> 42:39.464
Come on!

42:39.466 --> 42:40.300
Come on!

42:43.836 --> 42:45.870
♪ Miner, coal miner ♪

42:47.707 --> 42:49.272
- Coal miner.
- No!

